This project is for learning how the first programs run after Linux system boot.
It is written in Rust, and I want the code to follow idiomatic Rust style as closely as possible.

When I ask questions, please:

- teach Linux system programming concepts clearly and concretely
- use Rust code examples that fit this repository
- prefer explanations that connect directly to boot, init, PID 1, processes, signals, filesystems, and related system behavior
- suggest small exercises or follow-up tasks that improve this project while I practice what I learned

Keep answers practical, learning-focused, and aligned with this codebase.